A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 1 of Chapter 24A of Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to massage therapy practice generally, so as to prohibit massage therapy businesses
3 from operating during certain set hours; to revise definitions; to provide for related matters;
4 to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Article 1 of Chapter 24A of Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
8 massage therapy practice generally, is amended by revising paragraphs (5) through (12) of
9 Code Section 43-24A-3, relating to definitions, as follows:
10 "(5) 'Entity' means the owner or operator of a business where massage therapy for
11 compensation is performed.
12 (6)(5) 'License' means a valid and current certificate of registration issued by the board
13 pursuant to this chapter to practice massage therapy.
14 (7)(6) 'Licensee' means any person holding a license.
15 (8)(7) 'Massage therapist' means a person licensed under this chapter as a massage
16 therapist who administers or teaches massage or massage therapy for compensation.
